Hi Anna,

We have recently set up some new protocols to limit plugins being added to live sites for a couple of reasons:

  1. It ensures live sites are stable and stay online (new plugins are ideally tested in staging first).
  2. If there is a security breach of a live website, significantly less damage can be done when there are less plugins or not well coded plugins present.
  3. It reduces unnecessary or duplicate plugins being added. This decreases bloat and vulnerabilities.

I have lifted the restriction on your site, for now. Please let me know when you are done, and we will go ahead and reinstate the protocol.

Note, this also applies to all of your websites that we host and manage.
